<subSubSection id="C31BE28D7704FFFFFF14A6CF91E7F8BF" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBEB1067704FFFFFF14A6CF91E7F8BF" blockId="83.[151,1437,1444,1936]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<materialsCitation id="3B69BB5B7704FFFFFF14A6CF9225F99F" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424726228" country="Brazil" location="West" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="West">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFF14A6CF9176FA27" bold="true" box="[151,267,1444,1469]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFE1BA6CF919CFA27" box="[408,481,1444,1469]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFE1BA6CF919CFA27" box="[408,481,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has expanded rather spectacularly in the 
<collectingRegion id="49C57FE47704FFFFFC49A6CE947CFA26" box="[970,1025,1445,1468]" country="Tanzania" name="Mjini Magharibi" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">West</collectingRegion>
Atlantic in the past 20 years since successive Brazilian research groups published reports on samples obtained during various projects along the northeast and southeast coasts of 
<collectingCountry id="F316F1967704FFFFFD93A6879225F99F" box="[528,600,1516,1541]" name="Brazil" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation id="3B69BB5B7704FFFFFDE0A68691EBF8BF" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424726230" collectingDate="1977-05" country="Brazil" county="Several" location="The" municipality="Thus" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="No">
<collectingRegion id="49C57FE47704FFFFFDE0A68692F8F99E" box="[611,645,1517,1540]" country="Haiti" name="Nord" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">No</collectingRegion>
less than 10 species are now known from 
<collectingCountry id="F316F1967704FFFFFBE6A68794D4F99F" box="[1125,1193,1516,1541]" name="Brazil" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Muricy 
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFA97A6869530F99F" box="[1300,1357,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
2011). 
<location id="8EDEE7DD7704FFFFFF14A56490BEF9B2" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A800107704FFFFFF14A636909AF815:8EDEE7DD7704FFFFFF14A56490BEF9B2" box="[151,195,1551,1576]" country="Brazil" county="Several" municipality="Thus" name="The" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" stateProvince="No">The</location>
neighboring 
<location id="8EDEE7DD7704FFFFFEDFA57B9251F9B2" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A800107704FFFFFF14A636909AF815:8EDEE7DD7704FFFFFEDFA57B9251F9B2" box="[348,556,1551,1576]" country="Brazil" county="Several" municipality="Thus" name="Greater Caribbean" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" stateProvince="No">Greater Caribbean</location>
also has a considerable number, eight species, two of which are shared with 
<location id="8EDEE7DD7704FFFFFF14A55F9083F9D7" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A800107704FFFFFF14A636909AF815:8EDEE7DD7704FFFFFF14A55F9083F9D7" box="[151,254,1588,1613]" country="Brazil" county="Several" municipality="Thus" name="Brazilian" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" stateProvince="No">Brazilian</location>
waters. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BDA2B7C7704FFFFFEDEA55F91E5F9D7" box="[349,408,1588,1613]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Thus</collectingMunicipality>
, a total of 16 species are known from the 
<collectingRegion id="49C57FE47704FFFFFCF2A55E93B1F9D6" box="[881,972,1589,1612]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Western" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Western</collectingRegion>
Atlantic. The taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFA86A55F9533F9D7" box="[1285,1358,1588,1613]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFA86A55F9533F9D7" box="[1285,1358,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this region is held hostage by the uncertainty of the precise properties of the two eldest, but insufficiently described, species, viz. 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFEAFA5179297F90E" authority="Schmidt, 1880" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1880" box="[300,746,1660,1685]" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Stellettinopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="euastrum">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFEAFA5179247F90E" box="[300,570,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Stellettinopsis euastrum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFDC7A5179297F90E" author="Schmidt" box="[580,746,1660,1685]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="Schmidt, O. (1880) Die Spongien des Meerbusen von Mexico (Und des caraibischen Meeres). Heft II. Abtheilung II." type="journal volume" year="1880">Schmidt, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFCA5A51794E3F90E" authority="Weltner, 1882" authorityName="Weltner" authorityYear="1882" box="[806,1182,1660,1685]" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Stelletta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="transiens">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFCA5A517938FF90E" box="[806,1010,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Stelletta transiens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFC78A51794E3F90E" author="Weltner" box="[1019,1182,1660,1685]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="Weltner, W. (1882) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Spongien. Inaugural Dissertation Freiburg, pp. 1 - 62." type="book chapter" year="1882">Weltner, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCounty id="62DFC98A7704FFFFFB2FA517957DF90F" box="[1196,1280,1660,1685]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Several</collectingCounty>
subsequently described 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFE88A5F49129F922" box="[267,340,1695,1720]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFE88A5F49129F922" box="[267,340,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFE3CA5CA9366F922" authority="De Laubenfels, 1934" authorityName="De Laubenfels" authorityYear="1934" box="[447,795,1695,1720]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="alleni">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFE3CA5CA925DF922" box="[447,544,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">E. alleni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFDA9A5CB9366F922" author="De" box="[554,795,1695,1720]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="De Laubenfels, M. W. (1934) New sponges from the Puerto Rican Deep. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 91, 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="1934">De Laubenfels, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFCABA5CA94E7F922" authority="Boury-Esnault, 1973" authorityName="Boury-Esnault" authorityYear="1973" box="[808,1178,1695,1720]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="corneus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFCABA5CA93DEF922" box="[808,931,1697,1720]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">E. corneus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFC2FA5F494E7F922" author="Boury-Esnault" box="[940,1178,1695,1720]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="Boury-Esnault, N. (1973) Resultats scientifiques des campagnes de la &quot; Calypso &quot;." type="book" year="1973">Boury-Esnault, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFB2BA5CA91F1F946" authority="Mothes, Lerner &amp; Silva, 1999" authorityName="Mothes, Lerner &amp; Silva" authorityYear="1999" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="diminutus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFB2BA5CA954AF922" box="[1192,1335,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">E. diminutus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFAC2A5F491F1F946" author="Mothes" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="Mothes, B., Lerner, C. B. &amp; Silva, C. M. M. Da (1999) Revision of Brazilian Erylus (Porifera: Astrophorida: Demospongiae) with description of a new species. Memoirs of the Queensland Museu, 44, 369 - 380." type="journal article" year="1999">Mothes, Lerner &amp; Silva, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFE4AA5AE933DF946" authority="Wiedenmayer, 1977" authorityName="Wiedenmayer" authorityYear="1977" box="[457,832,1732,1757]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="goffrilleri">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFE4AA5AE922BF947" box="[457,598,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">E. goffrilleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFDDDA5AF933DF946" author="Wiedenmayer" box="[606,832,1732,1757]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="Wiedenmayer, F. (1977) Shallow-water sponges of the western Bahamas. Experientia Supplementum, 28, 1 - 287." type="journal article" year="1977">
Wiedenmayer, 
<date id="FFBF97C67704FFFFFC8BA5AF933DF946" box="[776,832,1732,1756]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" value="1977-05">
<collectingDate id="EFFB6E2E7704FFFFFC8BA5AF933DF946" box="[776,832,1732,1756]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" value="1977-05">1977</collectingDate>
</date>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
may turn out to be a junior synonym of one of these two names. In the continued absence of proper re-descriptions, that also applies to the three species described here from the 
<collectingCountry id="F316F1967704FFFFFF7EA4679129F8BE" box="[253,340,1804,1828]" name="Guyana" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Guyana</collectingCountry>
shelf
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31BE28D7704FFFFFF44A444909AF815" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BBEB1067704FFFFFF44A444909AF815" blockId="83.[151,1437,1444,1936]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<materialsCitation id="3B69BB5B7704FFFFFF44A444909AF815" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424726245" location="Central West" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Central West">
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFF44A4449235F8D2" authority="Schmidt, 1880" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1880" box="[199,584,1839,1864]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="euastrum">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFF44A44491FEF8D2" box="[199,387,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Erylus euastrum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFE16A4449242F8D2" author="Schmidt" box="[405,575,1839,1864]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="Schmidt, O. (1880) Die Spongien des Meerbusen von Mexico (Und des caraibischen Meeres). Heft II. Abtheilung II." type="journal volume" year="1880">Schmidt, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFDFDA4449367F8D2" box="[638,794,1839,1864]" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Stellettinopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFDFDA4449367F8D2" box="[638,794,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Stellettinopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is a junior secondary homonym of the Mediterranean 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFF14A43F926DF8F7" authority="Schmidt, 1868" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,528,1876,1901]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="euastrum">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFF14A43F912DF8F6" box="[151,336,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Erylus euastrum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF77704FFFFFEE2A43F9274F8F7" author="Schmidt" box="[353,521,1876,1901]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refString="Schmidt, O. (1868) Die Spongien der Kuste von Algier. Mit Nachtragen zu den Spongien des Adriatischen Meeres (Drittes Supplement). Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig, i - iv, 44 pp." type="book" year="1868">Schmidt, 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFDC1A43F92E0F8F7" box="[578,669,1876,1901]" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Stelletta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFDC1A43F92E0F8F7" box="[578,669,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Stelletta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which further complicates the taxonomy of 
<collectingRegion id="49C57FE47704FFFFFB24A43F9544F8F6" box="[1191,1337,1876,1901]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Central West</collectingRegion>
Atlantic 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA857704FFFFFF14A41C909DF80A" box="[151,224,1911,1936]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D147704FFFFFF14A41C909DF80A" box="[151,224,1911,1936]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
